name: Ashish

projects.title: Stasis
projects.description: Stasis is a psychological horror game set on an abandoned space station. Players navigate a chilling environment, manage resources, and solve puzzles while uncovering the mystery of a terrifying alien entity.

projects.title: CanCare for Good
projects.description: CanCare is a project built for JPMC's Code for Good competition. It features an enhanced UI/UX for 100% form completion, optimized matching algorithms for reduced latency, and an AI chatbot for instant client access; winner of the JPMC Code for Good Hackathon.

projects.title: Templit
projects.description: Templit is a customizable tool that lets users create professional product mockups effortlessly. Perfect for e-commerce sites, it provides a quick and user-friendly experience with curated sets of mockups for inspiration.

projects.title: SyslogAI
projects.description: SyslogAI is an AI-powered system for analyzing and managing network syslogs, offering classification, trend analysis, error filtering, and suggested solutions to enhance troubleshooting and reduce downtime; placed in the Meta Rotational Network Engineer hackathon competition.

projects.title: WonderPickle
projects.description: WonderPickle is an interactive multimedia platform that pairs stunning JWST space imagery with curated music for an immersive audio-visual experience; winner of the NASA JSC Hack hackathon challenge.

projects.title: Neuroharmony
projects.description: Neuroharmony is a platform designed to support neurodivergent individuals by matching them with supportive communities and providing AI assistance and resources.

projects.title: Baker Museum
projects.description: Baker Museum is a fullstack project focused on designing and implementing a sophisticated database system tailored for an art museum environment.

projects.title: NeuroScore
projects.description: NeuroScore is a Swift app that allows users to track their Glasgow Coma Scores and recovery progress with recorded vocal notes and growth visualizations.

projects.title: GitStudy
projects.description: GitStudy is a study group platform that allows users to create and join study groups, share resources, and collaborate on projects; winner of the hackMISSO 2024 hackathon.

projects.title: Stellar Scholars
projects.description: Stellar Scholars is an educational game built using React and OpenAI's GPT API. It teaches young minds about galaxies and gravity through an interactive and engaging platform; placed in the TAMUhack hackathon general track and L3 Harris company track, won best design, and best use of AI in Cloudflare

projects.title: TBI-Project
projects.description: TBI-Project explores data-driven methods to analyze Glasgow Coma Scale scores and identify risk factors, with a focus on predictive modeling.

projects.title: Tama-Catch-Em-All
projects.description: Tama-Catch-Em-All is an object-oriented Tamagotchi game where users take care of and level up their PokÃ©mon in a fun and interactive environment.

projects.title: Bloom
projects.description: Bloom is your digital wellness companion, combining gamified tasks and personalized tree nurturing to promote mental well-being. It offers an innovative way to cultivate mindfulness and positivity.

projects.title: Data & Society: Data Visualization Project
projects.description: This project leverages Kepler.gl for dynamic data visualizations and linear regression models. It includes a user-friendly website that bridges data insights and accessibility.

projects.title: MISSO x CougarCS Case Quest: Uni-Link
projects.description: Uni-Link is an online marketplace prototype for students, designed collaboratively for MISSO x CougarCS Case Quest; placed in the CaseQuest Hackathon/Ideathon competition.

aboutpara: Hey! I'm Ashish, a Software Engineer at JPMorganChase and a University of Houston computer science alum with a minor in math. I'm really interested in picking up new technologies, and outside of tech, I love pandas, volleyball, drawing, manga, and discovering new music.
